<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={5.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={7.55}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={8.68}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={5.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={7.55}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={8.68}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>35.02</li><li>60.05</li><li>85.6</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}^{{2}}={7.55}^{{2}}+{8.68}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({7.55}\right)}{\left({8.68}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{25}={57.0025}+{75.3424}-{131.068}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{107.3449}=-{131.068}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.81900158696249}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={35.015026690875}={35.02}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({35.015026690875}\right)}}}}{{5.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{7.55}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.66698711417629}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left(-{0.66698711417629}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={60.045798008524}\approx{60.05}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{35.015026690875}+{60.045798008524}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={85.599411870102}\approx{85.6}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

